Description: Crypto Key Stack is a software based hardware wallets help protect your keys while transacting.
Full Description: Crypto Key Stack is a software based hardware wallets help protect your keys while transacting. Crypto Key Stack LLC was co-founded by Chris Gonyo and NFL veteran Israel Idonije in an effort to reduce the billions of dollars lost due to improper private key storage. The number of assets being stored and tracked on the blockchain is growing at an exponential rate, and they are all being secured by private keys. Realizing that software-based hardware wallets are excellent for cybersecurity,  but become vulnerable in the event of a physical disaster, Chris and Israel designed Crypto Key Stack to help preserve access to your assets in the event of a hardware failure and physical disaster. It was created out of a need for an affordable, high-quality stainless steel backup device that allowed users to store multiple cryptographic keys permanently.

Description: IRIS is focused on strengthening civil society through narrative strategies and creative moving image storytelling for impact.
Full Description: IRIS is focused on strengthening civil society through narrative strategies and creative moving image storytelling for impact. IRIS supports donor partners’ efforts to deepen collaboration between storytellers, movements and civil society leaders, furthering the goals of dismantling inequality and making progress on key social justice issues. IRIS began in 2019 as an incubated initiative within the Ford Foundation’s International Programs. The goal was to design and model a fully-integrated storytelling and narrative strategy. Over two years, the Foundation supported 40 cross-strategy storytelling and narrative grants supporting impact around gender, racial and ethnic justice, natural resources and climate change, civic engagement and government, technology and society and the future of work. In 2021, based on this successful experiment, IRIS launched as a new donor collaborative. The Compton, Children’s Investment Fund, Ford, Open Society and Skoll Foundations are the founding donors of IRIS. It was founded in 2021 by Cara Mertes, and is located in New York, New York.

Description: Be On The Move is a Home Health physical therapy provider for Seniors in Palm Beach County Florida
Full Description: We understand the immense potential of physical therapy in fostering strength development, managing emerging conditions, and promoting post-surgical recovery. However, we also recognize the obstacles faced by therapists and Senior patients in realizing its full clinical benefits due to exhaustion and other challenges. We are aware that traditional physical therapy practices have led to over 40% of therapists experiencing work-related pain, while an alarming 50% of patients are unable to complete their prescribed care plans. It is evident that both therapists and patients require enhanced support to unlock the true power of physical therapy. Description: Evercred is a user-centric, simplified, and long-term credentialing and management system.
Full Description: We are solving the $5B frustrating & friction filled identity verification, onboarding & credentialing problem for physicians and those who employ them and pay them. We empower the individual physicians to be the direct primary source of their identity and credentials by leveraging open standards based decentralized identity technology. The plan is for our cutting edge technology, built on open standards to be leveraged to usurp huge sectors of our $3.9T healthcare system. BACKGROUND: It currently takes 2 to 6 months to onboard and credential a physician. This process then has to be repeated every two years for compliance purposes. This problem costs up to $1 million for health systems, and physicians lose an average of $100K in potential income per onboarding credentialing event.  Until now there has been no verifiable trusted and user centric source of authentic data regarding physician credentialing. We make the practicing physician the primary source of their data fixing this problem permanently. Our system will streamline the on boarding process and will fix regulatory privacy compliance issues permanently. The HPEC application can allow physicians to prove their identity in a trusted way moving forward when they log in to healthcare applications like EHR, Telemedicine, and other systems that would benefit from identity verification. We raised $650K to fund development of HPEC, the physician facing credential wallet in 2020, and have completed and launched the MVP to the app store. While in development we realized, in order to keep HPEC viable and accessible we also needed to build the credential issuing system, so we founded evercred; to address a broader and more comercial market, and developed and launched that as well. We are now entering a seed round shortly to fund evercred which is the next phase of this project.
